## Rules

- `block_ids` within one section must be **contiguous ascending integers**.
- No block may appear in more than one section.
- **Claim section-header blocks together with their content.** If a block like `(h2) Your Responsibilities`, `(h3) What you'll do`, `(p) MISSIONS:`, `(p) Qualifications:` immediately precedes a content block of the same topic, include the heading block in the section. Do **not** leave obvious section headings dangling as gaps.
- **Topic-boundary gaps are allowed.** Truly unclassifiable blocks — decorative banners, standalone separators, EEO / non-discrimination / GDPR / privacy boilerplate, "Please visit our website" links — can be left unassigned.
- Physical, mental, and environmental demands ("vision", "lift X lbs", "stand for Y hrs", "climate controlled office", "noise level") are **requirements**, not a separate kind. Include them together with the rest of the requirements section when adjacent.
- "Why join us" / "What makes us different" / "Our values" culture prose is `company`, not `benefits`. `benefits` is reserved for concrete perks and compensation.
- If a kind legitimately appears in two non-contiguous ranges (e.g. a company blurb at the top and another at the bottom), emit two entries — not one entry with a gap.

